            <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> December 1, 2025</p>
            <p><strong>App:</strong> FamilyEats - Meal Planning & Grocery List App</p>

            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>
                FamilyEats ("we," "our," or "us") is developed and operated by Sahab Solutions. This
                Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your
                information when you use our FamilyEats mobile application.
            </p>

            <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>We collect information you provide directly to us when using FamilyEats:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Account Information:</strong> Name, email address, and password when you
                    create an account
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Household Data:</strong> Household name, invite codes, and member
                    associations
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Recipe Data:</strong> Recipes you create including titles, descriptions,
                    ingredients, and quantities
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Meal Plan Data:</strong> Your scheduled meals and flexible meal
                    selections
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Custom Ingredients:</strong> Any custom ingredients you add to your
                    ingredient bank
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Subscription Information:</strong> Purchase history and subscription
                    status (processed through Apple App Store)
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Provide, maintain, and improve the FamilyEats app</li>
                <li>Sync your data across devices and household members</li>
                <li>Generate shopping lists based on your meal plans</li>
                <li>Process your subscription and manage Pro features</li>
                <li>Send important service-related notifications</li>
                <li>Respond to your inquiries and provide customer support</li>
                <li>Analyze usage patterns to improve app functionality</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Data Storage and Security</h2>
            <p>Your data is stored securely using Google Firebase services:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Firebase Authentication:</strong> Securely manages your login
                    credentials
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Cloud Firestore:</strong> Stores your recipes, meal plans, and household
                    data
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Firebase Security Rules:</strong> Ensures users can only access their
                    own household data
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your personal
                information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.
            </p>

            <h2>Household Data Sharing</h2>
            <p>
                FamilyEats is designed for household collaboration. When you join or create a
                household:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>All household members can view and edit shared recipes</li>
                <li>Meal plans are visible to all household members</li>
                <li>Shopping lists are synchronized across all members</li>
                <li>Your display name is visible to other household members</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                You control who joins your household through invite codes. Only share your invite
                code with people you trust.
            </p>

            <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p>FamilyEats integrates with the following third-party services:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Google Firebase:</strong> Authentication, database, and analytics</li>
                <li><strong>RevenueCat:</strong> Subscription management and in-app purchases</li>
                <li><strong>Apple App Store</strong> Payment processing for subscriptions</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                These services have their own privacy policies governing how they handle your data.
            </p>

            <h2>In-App Purchases and Subscriptions</h2>
            <p>
                FamilyEats offers a Pro subscription with additional features. Subscription
                purchases are processed through:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Apple App Store (iOS devices)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                We do not directly collect or store your payment information. All payment processing
                is handled by Apple or Google according to their respective privacy policies.
            </p>

            <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>
                FamilyEats is not intended for children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly
                collect personal information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian
                and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us.
            </p>

            <h2>Data Retention</h2>
            <p>
                We retain your data for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide
                you services. You can delete your data by:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Leaving a household (removes your association but keeps shared data)</li>
                <li>
                    Deleting a household (removes all recipes, meal plans, and member data - owner
                    only)
                </li>
                <li>Contacting us to request complete account deletion</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Your Rights</h2>
            <p>You have the right to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Access your personal information stored in the app</li>
                <li>Correct inaccurate information through the app settings</li>
                <li>Delete your account and associated data</li>
                <li>Export your recipe and meal plan data (contact us for assistance)</li>
                <li>Opt-out of non-essential communications</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Guest Mode</h2>
            <p>
                FamilyEats offers a Guest Mode for users who want to try the app without creating an
                account:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Guest data is stored locally and in our database temporarily</li>
                <li>Guest data is not backed up and will be lost if you sign out</li>
                <li>We recommend creating an account to preserve your data</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>
                We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any
                changes by updating the "Last updated" date and, for significant changes, through
                in-app notifications.
            </p>

